{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885309537,"sessionID":"ses_284fd1305fferLawGsstvfmYgv","part":{"id":"prt_d7b03563b001qlykgkaSotiOxF","messageID":"msg_d7b033ece001nNDNwvIWfUgwvI","sessionID":"ses_284fd1305fferLawGsstvfmYgv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a2fc98f10be744cdbff6bb7b55be53c4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-031 — RBAC 配置\n2: \n3: **Module:** `manifests`  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Router RBAC template\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide namespace-scoped RBAC resources for Router with conditional creation and validation.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Router RBAC conditional rendering\n22: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` exists\n23: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.rbac.create }}` is `true`\n24: - **THEN** ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding SHALL be rendered\n25: - **WHEN** value is `false`\n26: - **THEN** no RBAC resources SHALL be rendered for router\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName validation guard\n29: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled (`router.rbac.create: true`)\n30: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}` is empty or not set\n31: - **THEN** template SHALL fail with error: `\"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\"`\n32: - **WHEN** value is set\n33: - **THEN** template SHALL render successfully\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount creation\n36: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n37: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is templated\n38: - **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n39:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n40:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n41:   - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n42:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n43:   - `labels` from helper template `agentcube.labels`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Router Role namespace-scoped permissions\n46: - **GIVEN** Router needs Secret access within its namespace\n47: - **WHEN** Role is templated\n48: - **THEN** Role SHALL have:\n49:   - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n50:   - `kind: Role`\n51:   - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n52:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n53:   - `rules` array with single entry:\n54:     - `apiGroups: [\"\"]` (core API group)\n55:     - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n56:     - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding binding\n59: - **GIVEN** Router Role needs binding to ServiceAccount\n60: - **WHEN** RoleBinding is templated\n61: - **THEN** RoleBinding SHALL have:\n62:   - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n63:   - `kind: RoleBinding`\n64:   - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n65:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n66:   - `labels` from helper template\n67:   - `subjects`: ServiceAccount with name from values in release namespace\n68:   - `roleRef`:\n69:     - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n70:     - `kind: Role`\n71:     - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Router RBAC no cluster-wide access\n74: - **GIVEN** Router Role only grants namespace-scoped permissions\n75: - **WHEN** Role rules are evaluated\n76: - **THEN** no ClusterRole or ClusterRoleBinding SHALL be created for Router\n77: - **AND** Router SHALL NOT have access to resources in other namespaces\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### Requirement: WorkloadManager RBAC template\n82: \n83: The system SHALL provide cluster-wide RBAC resources for WorkloadManager with full CRD operation permissions.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation\n86: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` is rendered\n87: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n88: - **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n89:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n90:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n91:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n92:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n93:   - `labels` from helper template `agentcube.labels`\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole agent-sandbox permissions\n96: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs Sandbox CRD access\n97: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `agents.x-k8s.io` are defined\n98: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n99:   - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n100:   - `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`\n101:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole sandbox extension permissions\n104: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs extension CRD access\n105: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` are defined\n106: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n107:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n108:   - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\",\"sandboxtemplates\",\"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n109:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n110:   - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n111:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n114: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs CodeInterpreter CRD access\n115: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` are defined\n116: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n117:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n118:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n119:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n120:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`\n121:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n122:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`\n123:   - `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n126: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs AgentRuntime CRD read access\n127: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for AgentRuntime are defined\n128: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n129:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n130:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n131:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\"]`\n132:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n133:   - `verbs: [\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole core resource permissions\n136: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs Pod and Secret access\n137: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for core API are defined\n138: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n139:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n140:   - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n141:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\"]`\n142:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n143:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole TokenReview permission\n146: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs TokenReview for authentication\n147: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for authentication API are defined\n148: - **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n149:   - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n150:   - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n151:   - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding creation\n154: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager ClusterRole needs binding\n155: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is templated\n156: - **THEN** ClusterRoleBinding SHALL have:\n157:   - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n158:   - `kind: ClusterRoleBinding`\n159:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n160:   - `labels` from helper template\n161:   - `subjects`:\n162:     - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n163:     - `name: workloadmanager`\n164:     - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n165:   - `roleRef`:\n166:     - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n167:     - `kind: ClusterRole`\n168:     - `name: workloadmanager`\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ### Requirement: RBAC values.yaml configuration\n173: \n174: The system SHALL provide configurable RBAC flags in values.yaml.\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Router RBAC create flag default\n177: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` defines router section\n178: - **WHEN** `router.rbac.create` is defined\n179: - **THEN** default value SHALL be `false` (RBAC disabled by default)\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName configuration\n182: - **GIVEN** router RBAC can be enabled\n183: - **WHEN** `router.serviceAccountName` is defined in values.yaml\n184: - **THEN** default value SHALL be `\"\"` (empty string, user must set when enabling RBAC)\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Router RBAC enabled deployment\n187: - **GIVEN** user wants Router RBAC created by Helm\n188: - **WHEN** values.yaml is configured with:\n189:   - `router.rbac.create: true`\n190:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"agentcube-router\"`\n191: - **THEN** Helm install SHALL create ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding\n192: - **AND** Router Deployment SHALL use `serviceAccountName: agentcube-router`\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Router external RBAC deployment\n195: - **GIVEN** user has pre-existing ServiceAccount/RBAC externally managed\n196: - **WHEN** values.yaml is configured with:\n197:   - `router.rbac.create: false`\n198:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"my-existing-sa\"`\n199: - **THEN** Helm install SHALL NOT create RBAC resources\n200: - **AND** Router Deployment SHALL reference existing ServiceAccount\n201: \n202: ---\n203: \n204: ### Requirement: RBAC security compliance\n205: \n206: The system SHALL follow Kubernetes RBAC best practices with minimal permission grants.\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: No wildcard permissions\n209: - **GIVEN** RBAC templates define permission rules\n210: - **WHEN** ClusterRole or Role rules are inspected\n211: - **THEN** no rule SHALL use wildcard `\"*\"` for `resources` or `verbs`\n212: - **AND** all `apiGroups`, `resources`, `verbs` SHALL be explicitly listed\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Least privilege principle\n215: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs specific operations on resources\n216: - **WHEN** ClusterRole verbs are defined per resource\n217: - **THEN** verbs SHALL be minimum required for operation:\n218:   - Read-only resources: `get`, `list`, `watch` only\n219:   - Status subresources: `get`, `update`, `patch` only (no delete)\n220:   - Finalizers: `update` only\n221:   - Managed resources: full CRUD where lifecycle management required\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Namespace isolation for Router\n224: - **GIVEN** Router only needs secrets in its own namespace\n225: - **WHEN** Router Role is evaluated\n226: - **THEN** Role SHALL NOT grant access to cluster-wide resources\n227: - **AND** Role SHALL NOT grant access to resources in other namespaces\n228: - **AND** RoleBinding SHALL only bind within `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: TokenReview restricted to WorkloadManager\n231: - **GIVEN** TokenReview is sensitive authentication operation\n232: - **WHEN** RBAC permissions are audited\n233: - **THEN** TokenReview `create` verb SHALL only be granted to WorkloadManager\n234: - **AND** Router SHALL NOT have TokenReview permission\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ### Requirement: RBAC template validation\n239: \n240: The system SHALL provide template validation for RBAC configuration.\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Helm template rendering validation\n243: - **GIVEN** RBAC templates are complete\n244: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` is executed\n245: - **THEN** output SHALL contain valid YAML for:\n246:   - Router ServiceAccount\n247:   - Router Role\n248:   - Router RoleBinding\n249:   - WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n250:   - WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n251:   - WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Helm template failure on missing serviceAccountName\n254: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n255: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=true` is executed without `router.serviceAccountName`\n256: - **THEN** template SHALL fail with error message containing `\"router.serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Helm template skip when RBAC disabled\n259: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is disabled\n260: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=false` is executed\n261: - **THEN** output SHALL NOT contain Router ServiceAccount, Role, or RoleBinding\n262: - **AND** WorkloadManager RBAC SHALL still be rendered\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n265: - **GIVEN** RBAC templates are complete\n266: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n267: - **THEN** lint SHALL pass with no errors related to RBAC templates\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ### Requirement: E2E RBAC validation\n272: \n273: The system SHALL validate RBAC permissions in E2E tests.\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: E2E Router secret access\n276: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is deployed with `router.rbac.create=true`\n277: - **WHEN** Router Pod attempts to create/read/update/delete Secret in its namespace\n278: - **THEN** operations SHALL succeed (permission granted by Role)\n279: - **WHEN** Router Pod attempts to access Secret in different namespace\n280: - **THEN** operation SHALL fail (namespace isolation)\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager sandbox creation\n283: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n284: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to create Sandbox CRD\n285: - **THEN** operation SHALL succeed (permission granted by ClusterRole)\n286: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to update Sandbox status\n287: - **THEN** operation SHALL succeed\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager CodeInterpreter lifecycle\n290: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n291: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts full lifecycle on CodeInterpreter CRD\n292: - **THEN** create, get, list, update, delete SHALL succeed\n293: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to update CodeInterpreter finalizers\n294: - **THEN** operation SHALL succeed\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager Pod read access\n297: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n298: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to get/list/watch Pods\n299: - **THEN** operations SHALL succeed\n300: - **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to create/delete Pod directly\n301: - **THEN** operation SHALL fail (only read verbs granted)\n302: \n303: ---\n304: \n305: ## Constants Summary\n306: \n307: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n308: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n309: | `ROUTER_RBAC_CREATE_DEFAULT` | `false` | `values.yaml` | Router RBAC disabled by default |\n310: | `ROUTER_SA_NAME_DEFAULT` | `\"\"` | `values.yaml` | Router ServiceAccount name must be explicitly set |\n311: | `WORKLOADMANAGER_SA_NAME` | `workloadmanager` | `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Fixed ServiceAccount name for WorkloadManager |\n312: | `RBAC_API_VERSION` | `rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1` | RBAC templates | Stable RBAC API version |\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## Dependencies Summary\n317: \n318: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n319: |---------|---------|---------|\n320: | `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | RBAC API stability (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n321: | `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template conditionals and validation guards |\n322: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `agents.x-k8s.io` | Sandbox, SandboxClaim, SandboxTemplate, SandboxWarmPool resources |\n323: | `AgentCube CRDs` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | CodeInterpreter, AgentRuntime custom resources |\n324: \n325: ---\n326: \n327: ## File Changes Summary\n328: \n329: | File | Action | Description |\n330: |------|--------|-------------|\n331: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Modified | Add validation guard for serviceAccountName requirement |\n332: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Existing | WorkloadManager RBAC resources (no changes) |\n333: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Modified | Document `router.rbac.create` and `router.serviceAccountName` defaults |\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ## References\n338: \n339: - proposal.md — AR-031 proposal with scope and implementation checklist\n340: - manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml — Router RBAC template\n341: - manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml — WorkloadManager RBAC template\n342: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation — https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n343: - changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md — Helm Chart templates context\n344: \n345: ---\n346: \n347: ## Validation Checklist\n348: \n349: - [ ] `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes with no errors\n350: - [ ] Router RBAC renders when `router.rbac.create=true` with valid `serviceAccountName`\n351: - [ ] Router RBAC skipped when `router.rbac.create=false`\n352: - [ ] Template fails when `router.rbac.create=true` without `serviceAccountName`\n353: - [ ] Router Role only grants Secret permissions (namespace-scoped)\n354: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole grants all required CRD permissions\n355: - [ ] No wildcard (`*`) in any RBAC resources or verbs\n356: - [ ] TokenReview only granted to WorkloadManager, not Router\n357: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding references correct ServiceAccount\n358: - [ ] E2E test: Router can manage secrets in its namespace\n359: - [ ] E2E test: WorkloadManager can create/manage Sandboxes\n360: - [ ] E2E test: WorkloadManager can create/manage CodeInterpreters\n\n(End of file - total 360 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-031 — RBAC 配置\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Router RBAC template\n\nThe system SHALL provide namespace-scoped RBAC resources for Router with conditional creation and validation.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775885309527,"end":1775885309535}}}}
